00:57:07,524 --> 00:57:10,118
Up until three months ago,
there was no Michael Knight.

837
00:57:10,193 --> 00:57:13,685
Well, phony credentials
don't surprise me.

838
00:57:13,763 --> 00:57:15,924
He said he's here
to sell me something.

839
00:57:15,999 --> 00:57:19,457
- Since when did we go public?
- Since I saw that car perform.

840
00:57:19,536 --> 00:57:23,632
Tanya, it's one thing
to sneak out of a development lab
with secrets to sell,

841
00:57:23,706 --> 00:57:25,867
<i>but quite another</i>
<i>to steal an entire prototype.</i>

842
00:57:25,942 --> 00:57:28,376
<i>I don't like it.</i>
<i>It smells like a setup.</i>

843
00:57:28,445 --> 00:57:30,709
Did you run his fingerprints?

844
00:57:30,780 --> 00:57:33,476
I don't have any.
Anyway, that's a fallacy.

845
00:57:33,550 --> 00:57:36,519
Fingerprints are only on file
if somebody's got a criminal record.

846
00:57:36,586 --> 00:57:40,044
Or has worked for the government
in some law enforcement capacity.

847
00:57:40,123 --> 00:57:43,718
I can think of one way to get 'em,
but it might be a little messy.

848
00:57:45,094 --> 00:57:47,494
Well, I leave that entirely in your hands.

849
00:57:57,807 --> 00:58:00,571
Buddy, come on back here,
and you say thank you.

850
00:58:00,643 --> 00:58:03,976
Come on. Right now,
young man. Come on.

851
00:58:04,047 --> 00:58:06,641
Thank you!
I gotta go tell everybody!

852
00:58:06,716 --> 00:58:08,707
Okay.

853
00:58:12,422 --> 00:58:14,856
You don't look very happy.

854
00:58:14,924 --> 00:58:17,222
I thought it was a real nice day.

855
00:58:20,396 --> 00:58:22,387
Who are you really?

856
00:58:24,868 --> 00:58:26,927
I'm a friend.

857
00:58:27,003 --> 00:58:29,198
I'd like to be...
Michael.

858
00:58:31,074 --> 00:58:34,566
I still hurt from the last man
who made me feel...

859
00:58:38,381 --> 00:58:40,406
I can't go through it again.

860
00:58:42,285 --> 00:58:44,480
Maggie, it's okay.
I understand.

861
00:59:17,787 --> 00:59:20,187
Tell me I'm dreamin'.

862
00:59:20,256 --> 00:59:23,020
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>I see it, but I don't believe it.</i>

863
00:59:26,229 --> 00:59:28,527
She's gonna meet me
at the Rising Sun at 8:00.

864
00:59:28,598 --> 00:59:31,829
Michael, I don't think
it's likely that she'll meet you alone.
I know.

865
00:59:31,901 --> 00:59:35,564
But I doubt she'll get tough
until she satisfies herself
that I'm here alone.

866
00:59:35,638 --> 00:59:37,606
You may have a point there.

867
00:59:37,674 --> 00:59:39,869
Only a fool would be out there
all by himself.

868
00:59:39,943 --> 00:59:42,275
The old man and I
would disagree with you
on that one.

869
00:59:42,345 --> 00:59:46,372
There's two ways to fight a war, Devon.
With an army or all by yourself.

870
00:59:46,449 --> 00:59:48,679
But you can have an army.

871
00:59:48,751 --> 00:59:50,719
That's always been my point.

872
00:59:50,787 --> 00:59:53,847
But not the biggest army.
That's my point.

873
00:59:53,923 --> 00:59:56,721
If you can't outnumber 'em,
you're better off alone.
<i>[Engine Starts]</i>

874
00:59:58,261 --> 00:59:59,922
Hey!

875
00:59:59,996 --> 01:00:02,692
<i>Hey.!</i>

876
01:00:02,765 --> 01:00:04,756
Hey!

877
01:00:06,035 --> 01:00:08,765
You're gonna get
yourselves killed!

878
01:00:08,838 --> 01:00:10,465
Michael. Michael!

879
01:00:13,676 --> 01:00:16,406
Whoo-ooh!
Hey! Wow!

880
01:00:16,479 --> 01:00:18,447
Man, this thing
must make coffee too.

881
01:00:18,514 --> 01:00:21,642
I do nothing of the kind.
Now, pull over immediately.

882
01:00:21,718 --> 01:00:24,881
- Say what?
- I didn't say nothin'.

883
01:00:24,954 --> 01:00:26,945
Yeah, you did, man.
You said pull over.

884
01:00:27,023 --> 01:00:29,992
I didn't say pull over.
<i>Hey, don'tjive me, Browne.</i>

885
01:00:30,059 --> 01:00:33,153
Because if you didn't say pull over,
somebody else did.

886
01:00:33,229 --> 01:00:34,958
That's right. I did.

887
01:00:36,232 --> 01:00:39,224
Who are you, dude?
[KITT]
That's irrelevant.

888
01:00:43,139 --> 01:00:47,599
You are not the proper owners
of this vehicle,
so either you get out,

889
01:00:47,677 --> 01:00:49,668
or I will take the appropriate measures.

890
01:00:49,746 --> 01:00:52,943
Hey. Hey, hey.
All right!

891
01:00:53,016 --> 01:00:57,214
Now, I've heard of
some far-out burglar alarms,
but this is heavy!

892
01:00:57,286 --> 01:00:59,413
All right, mama.
Do your baddest.

893
01:00:59,489 --> 01:01:02,151
Good heavens.
And I thought Michael was difficult.

894
01:01:03,593 --> 01:01:05,584
[Tires Squealing]

895
01:01:08,531 --> 01:01:12,433
Gentlemen, I have attempted
to dissuade you
from this wayward behavior.

896
01:01:12,502 --> 01:01:14,493
Rave on, machine.
Rave on!

897
01:01:14,570 --> 01:01:17,130
Wh-What do you think he is?
Some kind of tape recorder?

898
01:01:17,206 --> 01:01:21,267
Who cares, man?
It's mine, and I will do with it
as I please.

899
01:01:21,344 --> 01:01:23,335
Watch this.

900
01:01:26,516 --> 01:01:28,507
Whoo-ooh!

901
01:01:30,386 --> 01:01:32,445
Yeah! Whoo-ooh! All right!

902
01:01:32,522 --> 01:01:35,116
[Speaking Spanish]

903
01:01:35,191 --> 01:01:38,683
Very juvenile.
Now watch this.

904
01:01:41,030 --> 01:01:43,692
Hey, man.
What's happening?

905
01:01:43,766 --> 01:01:45,859
Hey, look out!

906
01:01:45,935 --> 01:01:47,869
Whoa!

907
01:01:49,472 --> 01:01:51,531
<i>Where you goin</i>; <i>man?</i>
<i>What are you doing?</i>

908
01:01:51,607 --> 01:01:53,507
Hey, man.
I ain't doin' nothin'.

909
01:01:53,576 --> 01:01:56,636
Hey, well, don't go this way, man.
You're... You're taking us uptown.

910
01:01:56,713 --> 01:01:59,181
And I said I ain't doin' nothin'.

911
01:02:03,052 --> 01:02:05,748
Hey, man. Don't do that.
Man, I ain't doin' nothin'.

912
01:02:09,325 --> 01:02:11,316
I can't stop it!

913
01:02:14,597 --> 01:02:17,532
Come on, man.
Stop this thing, Jackson.
Step on the brake or something.

914
01:02:17,600 --> 01:02:20,068
- I'm steppin' on it!
- Well, then push somethin'.

915
01:02:20,136 --> 01:02:23,162
I don't know what to push.
You push something.

916
01:02:23,239 --> 01:02:25,332
<i>[Browne]</i>
<i>Hey, man. Where is this car</i>
<i>taking us?</i>

917
01:02:25,408 --> 01:02:28,434
- Hey, look out!
- [Tires Screech]

918
01:02:32,648 --> 01:02:34,616
Hey, man.
What's this car doing?

919
01:02:34,684 --> 01:02:36,675
[Both Yelling]

920
01:02:43,159 --> 01:02:45,150
[Groans]

921
01:03:09,485 --> 01:03:11,510
[KITT]
Of all the irresponsible behavior.

922
01:03:11,587 --> 01:03:15,216
To leave me with my keys in the ignition
and my doors open?

923
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:17,657
I'm sorry.
It won't happen again.

924
01:03:19,228 --> 01:03:21,162
KITT.

925
01:03:24,000 --> 01:03:26,468
KITT.

926
01:03:26,536 --> 01:03:28,561
I said I was sorry.

927
01:03:31,107 --> 01:03:34,599
- What do you want from me?
- A little consideration
would be a beginning.

928
01:03:34,677 --> 01:03:37,407
I have a lot on my mind,
and we got a lot of work to do.

929
01:03:37,480 --> 01:03:39,846
If it weren't for me,
you'd be walking.

930
01:03:39,916 --> 01:03:43,113
If it weren't for you,
I'd be missing our
most important rendezvous.

931
01:03:43,186 --> 01:03:45,120
The whole point of my mission.

932
01:03:45,188 --> 01:03:47,850
I am very, very grateful to you.

933
01:03:47,924 --> 01:03:50,358
Our mission.

934
01:03:50,426 --> 01:03:53,452
Our mission. Forgiven?

935
01:03:53,529 --> 01:03:55,463
I suppose so.

936
01:03:55,531 --> 01:03:58,932
- After all, we're only human, right?
- Don't press your luck.

937
01:03:59,001 --> 01:04:00,525
It was just a thought.

938
01:04:28,130 --> 01:04:31,759
<i>*</i> I'm gonna harden my heart <i>*</i>

939
01:04:32,802 --> 01:04:35,999
<i>*I'm gonna swallow my tears *</i>

940
01:04:37,006 --> 01:04:41,409
<i>*I'm gonna turn and leave you *</i>
Hi, fellas.

941
01:04:41,477 --> 01:04:44,139
<i>*Here **</i>
Nice race, huh?

942
01:04:44,213 --> 01:04:48,013
Well, uh, let's, uh,
go outside and talk about it.

943
01:04:48,084 --> 01:04:50,985
Well, I'm sorry,
but I'm here to meet a young lady.

944
01:04:51,053 --> 01:04:54,682
<i>Uh, Miss Walker got the message.</i>
<i>She sent us to pick you up.</i>

945
01:04:54,757 --> 01:04:58,488
Tanya did that?
You guys work for her too?

946
01:04:59,729 --> 01:05:01,993
Well, she suggested that we, uh,

947
01:05:02,064 --> 01:05:04,032
show you outsiders...

948
01:05:04,100 --> 01:05:07,365
what we do to people
that come in here and take away
our little prize money.

949
01:05:07,436 --> 01:05:12,430
Oh, didn't Tanya tell you?
I'm donating my share
of the prize money to the charity.

950
01:05:12,508 --> 01:05:15,204
Well, each of us got a little
donation for you too.

951
01:05:15,278 --> 01:05:16,711
<i>[Dolan Chuckling]</i>

952
01:05:16,779 --> 01:05:19,509
Hold this.
No, no. I'm first.

953
01:05:19,582 --> 01:05:22,415
Well, listen, guys,
I hate to mention this, but, uh,

954
01:05:22,485 --> 01:05:25,886
<i>I'm heavily trained in martial arts.</i>

955
01:05:25,955 --> 01:05:27,946
Martial arts!

956
01:05:28,024 --> 01:05:31,118
<i>[Banging, Thumping]</i>

957
01:05:32,194 --> 01:05:33,889
<i>*Hit me with your best shot *</i>

958
01:05:35,197 --> 01:05:37,188
<i>*Fire away *</i>

959
01:05:38,501 --> 01:05:42,028
<i>* You come on with a come-on</i>
<i>You don't fight fair *</i>

960
01:05:42,104 --> 01:05:45,870
<i>*But that's okay</i>
<i>See if I care *</i>

961
01:05:45,942 --> 01:05:48,968
<i>*Knock me down</i>
<i>It's all in vain **</i>

962
01:05:49,045 --> 01:05:50,307
[Groaning]

963
01:06:07,496 --> 01:06:10,624
I want that car examined
from top to bottom,
inside and out.

964
01:06:10,700 --> 01:06:12,895
Yes, sir.
What's that gonna tell us?

965
01:06:12,969 --> 01:06:14,960
Who Michael Knight is working for.

966
01:06:15,037 --> 01:06:16,834
The car is gonna tell us that?

967
01:06:16,906 --> 01:06:20,000
Well, even cars that are
specially designed
require stock parts,

968
01:06:20,076 --> 01:06:21,839
<i>and they have serial numbers.</i>

969
01:06:21,911 --> 01:06:27,315
Benjamin's engineers should be able to
give us a pretty good idea
where the work was done and by whom.

970
01:06:29,552 --> 01:06:32,919
- You're where?
<i>- [Michael]</i>
<i>I'm in jail.</i>

971
01:06:32,989 --> 01:06:35,457
<i>But it's a trumped-up charge.</i>
<i>It always is.</i>

972
01:06:35,524 --> 01:06:38,015
Look, I'm dead serious.

973
01:06:38,094 --> 01:06:41,154
The people we're after here
are practically running the town.

974
01:06:41,230 --> 01:06:43,164
Michael, where is the Knight 2000?

975
01:06:43,232 --> 01:06:46,463
I, uh... I'm not sure.
What do you mean you're not sure?

976
01:06:46,535 --> 01:06:49,698
How can you call me long distance
and tell me you've misplaced it?

977
01:06:49,772 --> 01:06:52,866
I didn't misplace it.
They impounded it.

978
01:06:52,942 --> 01:06:56,639
The trouble is, I think Comtron
talked the sheriff into letting them
check out the car.

979
01:06:56,712 --> 01:07:00,113
Congratulations. You're living up to
my every expectation.

980
01:07:00,182 --> 01:07:01,877
There's no time for insults.

981
01:07:01,951 --> 01:07:04,613
What are we gonna do?
"We." That's wonderful.

982
01:07:04,687 --> 01:07:08,646
A couple of days ago, you practically
drove over my foot to be on your own.
All right.

983
01:07:08,724 --> 01:07:10,919
I'm sorry.
I was a little hasty.

984
01:07:10,993 --> 01:07:14,053
Time's up, boy.
Let's get back to your cell.

985
01:07:14,130 --> 01:07:16,121
Devon, I'm telling you.
I'm counting on you.

986
01:07:16,198 --> 01:07:18,962
You come through now,
we got these people
right where we want 'em.

987
01:07:19,035 --> 01:07:21,936
It'll take me a while to get there.

988
01:07:22,004 --> 01:07:25,804
- We may have to resort to
other means... temporarily.
- What do you mean by that?

989
01:07:27,243 --> 01:07:30,144
Devon. Devon.

990
01:07:30,212 --> 01:07:33,010
Hey, did you guys cut me off?

991
01:07:33,082 --> 01:07:34,982
I demand another phone call.

992
01:07:37,319 --> 01:07:39,810
<i>[Whirring]</i>

993
01:07:48,664 --> 01:07:51,565
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>We've gone through three</i>
<i>diamond-bit drills.</i>

994
01:07:51,634 --> 01:07:53,625
Perhaps I can explain.

995
01:07:59,175 --> 01:08:03,077
- What's this mean? I don't understand.
- The sheriff fingerprinted Knight
when he was arrested.

996
01:08:03,145 --> 01:08:07,013
- These are the results.
- What's this mean? "No identification possible."

997
01:08:07,083 --> 01:08:09,074
Keep reading.

998
01:08:10,086 --> 01:08:13,487
- "Altered."
- "Expertly done."

999
01:08:14,490 --> 01:08:16,583
But still not the man's own prints.

1000
01:08:22,098 --> 01:08:24,430
Hey, cowboy.

1001
01:08:24,500 --> 01:08:26,491
Hey, I'm talking to you.

1002
01:08:32,842 --> 01:08:36,073
Hey, I want to know
what that machine of yours is made of.

1003
01:08:37,813 --> 01:08:40,907
Sit and spin.

1004
01:08:44,220 --> 01:08:47,917
It's unraveling.
Somebody from a very high level
is breathing down our necks.

1005
01:08:47,990 --> 01:08:49,924
Now, it's time to get out.

1006
01:08:49,992 --> 01:08:53,450
But we're just a few days from penetrating
all of Comtron's top secrets.

1007
01:08:53,529 --> 01:08:55,463
We go for the main one.

1008
01:08:55,531 --> 01:08:58,830
I have the access code
to the bubble memory chip
from Benjamin.

1009
01:08:58,901 --> 01:09:01,461
<i>It's worth more</i>
<i>than all the others combined.</i>

1010
01:09:01,537 --> 01:09:04,904
Now, we get it out of the computer,
and we'll fly out tonight.

1011
01:09:04,974 --> 01:09:07,067
Tanya, you're panicking over nothing.

1012
01:09:07,143 --> 01:09:11,773
<i>Lfhe had any proof of anything,</i>
<i>he wouldn't be wasting his time</i>
<i>at demolition derbies...</i>

1013
01:09:11,847 --> 01:09:13,815
or letting himself get locked up.

1014
01:09:13,883 --> 01:09:17,080
- He'd tell the sheriff why he was here.
- Trust me.

1015
01:09:17,153 --> 01:09:19,314
I had a feeling
when I looked in his eyes.

1016
01:09:19,388 --> 01:09:21,788
He's no ordinary cop.

1017
01:09:21,857 --> 01:09:24,257
He's far more dangerous.

1018
01:09:24,326 --> 01:09:26,317
Now he has to be eliminated.

1019
01:09:27,730 --> 01:09:30,198
Now you go get
Michael Knight out of jail,

1020
01:09:30,266 --> 01:09:33,633
<i>and I'll get the microchip design</i>
<i>out of the computer.</i>

1021
01:09:39,742 --> 01:09:42,677
You're making things worse.
First time in the can?

1022
01:09:43,679 --> 01:09:47,638
No. I used to nose around for
Army Intelligence back in 'Nam.

1023
01:09:49,318 --> 01:09:51,616
I got caught once by the 'Cong.

1024
01:09:51,687 --> 01:09:53,712
Yeah? What happened?

1025
01:09:53,789 --> 01:09:57,054
<i>I had to punish 'em.</i>
Oh, yeah?

1026
01:09:58,260 --> 01:10:01,991
Yeah, well, look,
I hope you don't take
what we did to you tonight personally.

1027
01:10:03,399 --> 01:10:05,959
No, man. You look like
you already paid your price.

1028
01:10:06,035 --> 01:10:08,230
Yeah. You got any friends
on the outside at all?

1029
01:10:08,304 --> 01:10:11,364
I mean, you made one phone call,
but I don't think anybody showed up.

1030
01:10:11,440 --> 01:10:14,341
- Yeah, I got one friend.
- Hey, that's good.

1031
01:10:14,410 --> 01:10:17,243
But we're not on
the best of terms right now.

1032
01:10:17,313 --> 01:10:19,543
Oh. That's bad.

1033
01:10:25,721 --> 01:10:28,155
[Whirring]

1034
01:10:28,224 --> 01:10:30,215
[Power Surging]

1035
01:10:33,996 --> 01:10:36,055
[Engine Starts]

1036
01:10:37,132 --> 01:10:38,565
[Beeps]

1037
01:10:52,414 --> 01:10:55,076
[Tires Squealing]

1038
01:11:04,526 --> 01:11:06,926
[Whirring]

1039
01:11:09,331 --> 01:11:13,734
Those other drivers...
the ones that tried to beat me up...

1040
01:11:13,802 --> 01:11:15,736
they local boys?
Nah.

1041
01:11:15,804 --> 01:11:18,102
We all got hired by Wilson,
the new security chief.

1042
01:11:18,173 --> 01:11:20,664
I heard about it in stir
when I was gettin' my parole.

1043
01:11:20,743 --> 01:11:23,303
Pay is good,
don't have to break too many laws.

1044
01:11:23,379 --> 01:11:27,907
You ever wonder why
a nice, polite electronics company
needs strong-arm boys?

1045
01:11:27,983 --> 01:11:29,974
[Chuckles]

1046
01:11:32,187 --> 01:11:34,553
I don't ask those kind of questions.

1047
01:11:47,870 --> 01:11:50,338
[Tires Squealing]

1048
01:12:04,687 --> 01:12:08,282
Deputy, I have a court order
for Mr. Knight's release.

1049
01:12:13,395 --> 01:12:17,195
Okay. I guess he's yours.

1050
01:12:19,668 --> 01:12:21,829
<i>[Tires Squealing]</i>

1051
01:12:30,579 --> 01:12:32,376
<i>[Crash]</i>

1052
01:12:36,952 --> 01:12:39,386
What's going on back there?

1053
01:12:44,059 --> 01:12:47,688
- I don't believe this.
- Must be a drunk.
See if he hurt himself.

1054
01:12:47,763 --> 01:12:51,722
I won't even ask you
how you did this, KITT, but thanks.
You're welcome.

1055
01:12:51,800 --> 01:12:53,665
Who you talking to?
There's nobody in there.

1056
01:12:53,736 --> 01:12:55,727
What in the...

1057
01:13:02,144 --> 01:13:05,238
<i>[Deputy]</i>
<i>Those bullets arejust</i>
<i>bouncing off that windshield.!</i>

1058
01:13:18,994 --> 01:13:20,985
Knight's escaped.
Let's go.

1059
01:13:28,804 --> 01:13:30,795
[Siren Wailing]

1060
01:13:47,089 --> 01:13:49,819
Well, it's no use
trying to catch that machine.

1061
01:13:51,026 --> 01:13:53,119
Then how are we gonna stop him?

1062
01:13:53,195 --> 01:13:56,596
He must be heading out of town.
There's nothing else out this way.

1063
01:13:58,600 --> 01:14:00,534
Oh, yes, there is.

1064
01:14:09,344 --> 01:14:11,369
<i>[Michael]</i>
<i>Now how do I get up there?</i>

1065
01:14:11,447 --> 01:14:15,383
It's times like this I wish I listened
more closely to Devon.

1066
01:14:15,451 --> 01:14:17,146
Is it all right to respond?

1067
01:14:17,219 --> 01:14:19,847
Yes, yes. It's all right.
Look, KITT,

1068
01:14:19,922 --> 01:14:23,551
I gotta get up to a roof about
a hundred feet.

1069
01:14:23,625 --> 01:14:27,527
Very well. If you'll set the pressure
adjustment for precisely 600 pounds,

1070
01:14:27,596 --> 01:14:29,564
you should land quite gently.

1071
01:14:29,631 --> 01:14:33,590
That's it?
I just set the pressure
and hit the button?

1072
01:14:33,669 --> 01:14:35,933
It would help
if you also opened the auto roof.

1073
01:14:36,004 --> 01:14:38,131
Smart-aleck car.

1074
01:14:38,207 --> 01:14:41,005
[Beeps]

1075
01:14:42,377 --> 01:14:44,311
- Okay.
- [Beeps]

1076
01:15:00,229 --> 01:15:02,459
You guys aren't gonna
believe this, but it's back.

1077
01:15:02,531 --> 01:15:05,591
What...
What do you mean it's back?
Back where?

1078
01:15:05,667 --> 01:15:07,760
Right out here
on the south parking lot.

1079
01:15:28,257 --> 01:15:30,885
Okay. Let's see.

1080
01:15:32,394 --> 01:15:33,884
Third floor.

1081
01:15:42,337 --> 01:15:44,271
<i>[Tanya]</i>
<i>Where's Knight?</i>

1082
01:15:44,339 --> 01:15:46,830
I don't know.
He busted out of jail.
You think he's here?

1083
01:15:46,909 --> 01:15:50,345
- There's no way he can get in
without being seen.
- How much do you wanna stake on that?

1084
01:15:50,412 --> 01:15:52,880
<i>I'm gonna go back up</i>
<i>to secure the microchip design.</i>

1085
01:15:52,948 --> 01:15:55,815
Now, you tell the guards
to shoot to kill.

1086
01:16:22,578 --> 01:16:24,569
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

1087
01:16:55,978 --> 01:16:58,105
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

1088
01:17:03,018 --> 01:17:04,952
Yes.

1089
01:17:05,020 --> 01:17:09,013
No, everything's okay.
I've got the microfilm,
the new memory chip.

1090
01:17:09,091 --> 01:17:12,754
I'll be leaving for the airfield soon.
Alert the pilot.

1091
01:17:12,828 --> 01:17:15,592
<i>Tell him I'm flying out</i>
<i>on Benjamin's orders.</i>

1092
01:17:15,664 --> 01:17:17,962
<i>Pick up Knight</i>
<i>and meet me at the</i> f<i>ield.</i>

1093
01:17:18,033 --> 01:17:20,797
<i>Very kind of you to organize</i>
<i>the evidence for me, Tanya.</i>

1094
01:17:20,869 --> 01:17:22,496
<i>Look. Don't do this.</i>

1095
01:17:22,571 --> 01:17:26,098
Whoever you work for
can't be worth what I can do for you.

1096
01:17:26,174 --> 01:17:29,109
Would you prefer this?

1097
01:17:29,177 --> 01:17:31,168
It's not a starry night in Nevada,

1098
01:17:32,280 --> 01:17:34,305
but it'll hurt just as much.

1099
01:17:37,552 --> 01:17:39,076
Michael Long.

1100
01:17:41,056 --> 01:17:43,251
Look, please don't do this.

1101
01:17:43,325 --> 01:17:45,316
If I hadn't done it,
Wilson would have.

1102
01:17:45,394 --> 01:17:47,794
<i>He would have shot you.</i>
<i>He gives the orders.</i>

1103
01:17:47,863 --> 01:17:51,890
<i>We... We could share millions.</i>
How can we share the millions, Tanya,
if you're not the boss?

1104
01:17:51,967 --> 01:17:55,300
Come on, Tanya.
You're the boss.
No one else.

1105
01:17:55,370 --> 01:17:57,361
All right. I'm the boss.

1106
01:17:58,540 --> 01:18:00,531
But we need somebody like you.

1107
01:18:00,609 --> 01:18:04,773
<i>I promise you a very rewarding...</i>
<i>partnership.</i>

1108
01:18:04,846 --> 01:18:07,679
Not this time.
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

1109
01:18:07,749 --> 01:18:09,944
All right. Hold it right there.
<i>[Tanya]</i>
<i>Shoot him.</i>

1110
01:18:18,126 --> 01:18:20,287
I want every guard to check in.

1111
01:18:28,603 --> 01:18:31,401
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>I'll take Personnel.</i>
<i>You take Accounting.</i>

1112
01:18:52,661 --> 01:18:54,652
[Groans]

1113
01:19:06,074 --> 01:19:09,043
[Man On Walkie-talkie]
Nothing in Personnel.
What about you, Baker?

1114
01:19:09,111 --> 01:19:11,136
<i>Baker? Baker.</i>

1115
01:19:11,213 --> 01:19:13,613
Nothing here.

1116
01:19:13,682 --> 01:19:15,445
Well, that wasn't Baker.

1117
01:19:18,386 --> 01:19:20,377
Halt.
[Panting]
Don't shoot. Don't shoot.

1118
01:19:20,455 --> 01:19:23,390
- It's Baker.
- What's goin' on?

1119
01:19:23,458 --> 01:19:27,053
Wilson. He wants yo<i>u u</i>p in...
in the administration building.

1120
01:19:27,129 --> 01:19:30,963
[Wilson On Walkie-talkie]
All guards be aware that Baker's
uniform has been stolen. Repeat.

1121
01:19:31,032 --> 01:19:34,092
The suspect is now wearing
a guard's uniform.

1122
01:19:34,169 --> 01:19:37,297
W... W...
Hold it right there, Knight.

1123
01:19:37,372 --> 01:19:40,307
<i>I've got him.</i>
<i>Dead in my sight.</i>
<i>Right out here next to his car.</i>

1124
01:19:40,375 --> 01:19:44,471
Don't let him move so much
as an inch, and you've got yourself
10,000 in cash, boy.

1125
01:19:44,546 --> 01:19:47,140
Yes, sir.

1126
01:19:47,215 --> 01:19:49,080
Let's go.

1127
01:19:49,151 --> 01:19:51,085
Almost made it.

1128
01:19:51,153 --> 01:19:54,054
But I was just a little
too smart for you, fella.

1129
01:19:54,122 --> 01:19:56,147
Sorry.

1130
01:19:56,224 --> 01:19:58,215
Don't look behind you.

1131
01:19:58,293 --> 01:20:00,284
[Whirring]

1132
01:20:01,563 --> 01:20:03,497
<i>Oh, no. No.</i>

1133
01:20:03,565 --> 01:20:05,726
There's no one behind me
for 200 yards.

1134
01:20:05,801 --> 01:20:10,261
- What about the car?
- There's no one in there either.
I looked.

1135
01:20:16,545 --> 01:20:19,241
[Gasps]
No, no, don't kill me.

1136
01:20:19,314 --> 01:20:22,545
Don't kill me.
I got a dog at home.
I got a sick mother.

1137
01:20:22,617 --> 01:20:25,643
All right.
Toss your weapon down
and get against the wall.

1138
01:20:34,296 --> 01:20:36,287
[Groaning]

1139
01:20:46,174 --> 01:20:48,233
<i>[Siren Wailing]</i>

1140
01:20:49,744 --> 01:20:52,110
That Trans-Am's loose
and heading right for us.

1141
01:20:59,221 --> 01:21:00,813
Look out!

1142
01:21:11,566 --> 01:21:15,161
KITT. KITT, you there?

1143
01:21:15,237 --> 01:21:17,728
Where would I go?

1144
01:21:17,806 --> 01:21:19,740
Look, I know we've had
some misunderstandings,

1145
01:21:19,808 --> 01:21:22,743
but I'm not so sure
I'm gonna be around
at the end of this trip.

1146
01:21:22,811 --> 01:21:26,247
If it's of any assurance,
your vital signs are still quite good,

1147
01:21:26,314 --> 01:21:29,044
but you do need
immediate medical attention.
[Beeping]

1148
01:21:29,117 --> 01:21:31,051
We can't stop, pal.

1149
01:21:31,119 --> 01:21:33,917
They're gonna be
coming at us from all directions now.

1150
01:21:34,923 --> 01:21:38,051
What can I do?
Any way you can get in touch
with Devon?

1151
01:21:38,126 --> 01:21:42,153
You could reach him
on the microwave mobile line.
He's en route to Millston.

1152
01:21:42,230 --> 01:21:44,061
Good. Do it. Do it fast.

1153
01:21:47,102 --> 01:21:48,865
What in the name of heaven
is going on?

1154
01:21:48,937 --> 01:21:53,374
Devon. Devon, they were gonna kill me.
They would have if it weren't for KITT.

1155
01:21:53,441 --> 01:21:57,002
Michael, what's wrong?
KITT, what's the matter with Michael?

1156
01:21:57,078 --> 01:21:59,012
I'm afraid Mr. Knight's been injured.

1157
01:21:59,080 --> 01:22:01,207
His vital signs are deteriorating rapidly.

1158
01:22:01,283 --> 01:22:04,116
He's losing blood.
I really feel I should take over.

1159
01:22:04,185 --> 01:22:06,585
You're not taking over anything.
You hear me?

1160
01:22:06,655 --> 01:22:09,055
Michael, forget everything.
Save yourself.

1161
01:22:09,124 --> 01:22:11,456
We can regroup to fight another day.

1162
01:22:11,526 --> 01:22:13,494
Don't worry, Devon.

1163
01:22:13,561 --> 01:22:16,257
- I'm gonna take us out winners.
- What have you learned?

1164
01:22:16,331 --> 01:22:19,061
Tanya and her buddies
are about to rip off Comtron.

1165
01:22:19,134 --> 01:22:20,965
Can you prove that?

1166
01:22:21,036 --> 01:22:23,834
Right now they're trying to
get away with millions of dollars...

1167
01:22:23,905 --> 01:22:25,873
worth of Comtron secrets.

1168
01:22:25,941 --> 01:22:29,900
- I'll contact the local police immediately.
- Forget that. They've been bought.

1169
01:22:29,978 --> 01:22:32,708
Contact the F.B.I. Or the state police,
have them standing by.

1170
01:22:32,781 --> 01:22:35,443
Standing by where?
They're making a run for it
to the airport.

1171
01:22:35,517 --> 01:22:38,543
I'm going after 'em.
<i>[Devon]</i>
<i>KITT, can he make it?</i>

1172
01:22:38,620 --> 01:22:41,088
You want the truth?
In front of him?

1173
01:22:41,156 --> 01:22:43,954
If I'm goin' out,
I'm taking them with me.

1174
01:22:51,232 --> 01:22:53,166
This is Chief of Security Wilson.

1175
01:22:53,234 --> 01:22:55,668
Patch me in
to Comtron truck dispatch.

1176
01:22:55,737 --> 01:22:59,673
I want everything we've got on the road
to stand by for special instructions.

1177
01:23:19,761 --> 01:23:22,457
[Chuckles]

1178
01:23:22,530 --> 01:23:25,124
<i>- [Michael]</i>
<i>Great.</i>
- What is?

1179
01:23:25,200 --> 01:23:27,760
I just figured out how
they intend to stop me.

1180
01:23:27,836 --> 01:23:30,862
Okay, KITT.
With all due respect,

1181
01:23:30,939 --> 01:23:33,032
<i>you aren't possibly considering...</i>

1182
01:23:34,909 --> 01:23:36,934
Oh, my word. You are.

1183
01:23:37,012 --> 01:23:40,709
That's right, baby.
Come to papa.

1184
01:23:43,551 --> 01:23:45,542
Hey.

1185
01:23:45,620 --> 01:23:47,815
Hey. That guy's nuts!

1186
01:23:47,889 --> 01:23:52,656
If you're going through with this,
may I suggest you permit me
to activate the turbo boost?

1187
01:23:52,727 --> 01:23:55,195
- The what?
- Never mind. Allow me to demonstrate.

1188
01:24:08,843 --> 01:24:10,777
[Coughs]

1189
01:24:13,915 --> 01:24:15,246
I'm gonna kill him.

1190
01:24:15,316 --> 01:24:18,342
I gotta admit,
this car is something else.

1191
01:24:18,420 --> 01:24:21,014
KITT. KITT, are you there?

1192
01:24:21,089 --> 01:24:25,321
- Come on, buddy.
We both can't pass out.
- We aren't speaking.

1193
01:24:26,995 --> 01:24:29,122
At least I know you're all right.

1194
01:24:29,197 --> 01:24:31,165
Then you really do care.

1195
01:24:31,232 --> 01:24:35,669
- Yeah, I care,
but don't tell anybody, okay?
- Okay.

1196
01:24:39,074 --> 01:24:40,939
Dolan. Come in, Dolan.

1197
01:24:41,009 --> 01:24:43,637
<i>Did you get him?</i>

1198
01:24:43,711 --> 01:24:45,736
I blocked the road and cut him off.

1199
01:24:45,814 --> 01:24:49,682
Good work.
Yeah, but he went right through
the side of my trailer.

1200
01:24:49,751 --> 01:24:53,050
- Have you been drinking?
- Not yet, but I plan on it.

1201
01:24:53,121 --> 01:24:56,682
I'm telling ya. There ain't no way
you're gonna stop that thing.

1202
01:25:01,930 --> 01:25:05,263
<i>[Wilson On Radio]</i>
<i>Attention all drivers. Attention all drivers.</i>

1203
01:25:05,333 --> 01:25:08,131
Anybody wanting a $15,000 bonus...

1204
01:25:08,203 --> 01:25:10,137
is to smash that Trans-Am head-on.

1205
01:25:10,205 --> 01:25:12,139
Do you read me?
I said head-on.

1206
01:25:12,207 --> 01:25:15,699
<i>He's currently heading north</i>
<i>on Highway 17.</i>

1207
01:25:15,777 --> 01:25:20,009
This is Truck 41 on 17.
You're nuts.

1208
01:25:20,081 --> 01:25:22,481
What good's $15,000
if you're dead?

1209
01:25:22,550 --> 01:25:24,484
<i>Well, jump clear, you idiot.</i>

1210
01:25:24,552 --> 01:25:26,577
But make sure you level that Trans-Am.

1211
01:25:26,654 --> 01:25:28,645
Forget it.

1212
01:25:31,192 --> 01:25:36,459
Make it $25,000 to the first man
that smashes and levels that Trans-Am.

1213
01:25:36,531 --> 01:25:39,500
<i>Do you read me? $25,000.</i>

1214
01:25:40,635 --> 01:25:44,127
- All right. I'll give it a shot.
- Devon, did you hear that?

1215
01:25:44,205 --> 01:25:47,732
<i>[Devon]</i>
<i>I'm afraid so.</i>
<i>You know what KITTcan do. Can he do it?</i>

1216
01:25:47,809 --> 01:25:51,677
I can't recall ever having put him
to that precise test.

1217
01:25:51,746 --> 01:25:53,611
Oh, great.

1218
01:25:53,681 --> 01:25:56,980
I suggest we'd better reach the airport
before we reach the truck.

1219
01:25:57,051 --> 01:25:59,417
You know something, KITT.

1220
01:25:59,487 --> 01:26:01,512
I think you're right.

1221
01:26:01,589 --> 01:26:05,753
<i>[Wilson]</i>
<i>Where are you, 41?</i>
<i>Just coming up to the airport turnoff.</i>

1222
01:26:05,827 --> 01:26:08,318
<i>Oh, yeah. I see you.</i>

1223
01:26:08,396 --> 01:26:11,763
You've got him.
Just over the next rise.

1224
01:26:11,833 --> 01:26:14,825
Here. Just in case he gets by.

1225
01:26:17,839 --> 01:26:19,932
We should be seeing them
any minute now.

1226
01:26:21,409 --> 01:26:25,209
No one survives a head-on collision
with a semi. No one.

1227
01:26:25,280 --> 01:26:27,271
Mr. Knight, this is foolhardy.

1228
01:26:27,348 --> 01:26:32,047
- I really must assume control.
- Negative. I'm driving this machine.

1229
01:26:32,120 --> 01:26:35,783
Devon, Michael is in no condition
to be making decisions.

1230
01:26:35,857 --> 01:26:39,725
KITT, I'm afraid as long as
he's conscious and in the driver's seat,
we have no choice.

1231
01:26:39,794 --> 01:26:42,024
An absurd set of circumstances.

1232
01:26:42,096 --> 01:26:44,121
Too bad, KITT.

1233
01:26:44,199 --> 01:26:48,101
The guy who designed you
believed in the strength of the individual.

1234
01:26:48,169 --> 01:26:50,831
We may have to put that to the test.

1235
01:26:54,108 --> 01:26:55,973
<i>[Wilson]</i>
<i>He isn't stopping.</i>

1236
01:26:56,044 --> 01:26:58,638
The man's nuts.
Well, I hope so.

1237
01:26:58,713 --> 01:27:02,547
- Any last thoughts, KITT?
- I wish you hadn't put it that way.

1238
01:27:05,486 --> 01:27:10,219
- He's heading right for him.
- We'll need a magnifying glass
and tweezers just to find him.

1239
01:27:10,291 --> 01:27:11,417
Or a blotter.

1240
01:27:13,127 --> 01:27:14,822
I got him in sight.

1241
01:27:14,896 --> 01:27:17,592
Remember, 25 big ones
if you nail him.

1242
01:27:30,311 --> 01:27:33,769
- That car just jumped over the truck.
- Don't be ridiculous.

1243
01:27:35,650 --> 01:27:38,619
- That's about as close
as you can get.
- Tell me about it.

1244
01:27:38,686 --> 01:27:41,416
Take her down. It's up to us.

1245
01:27:51,833 --> 01:27:54,063
- He hit us.
- No, you hit us.

1246
01:27:54,135 --> 01:27:57,400
Shut up and make another pass.
You want to make another pass,
you can jump out.

1247
01:27:57,472 --> 01:27:59,440
We'll be lucky to make the airport.

1248
01:28:32,640 --> 01:28:34,904
You get him?
Does it look like it?

1249
01:28:34,976 --> 01:28:37,774
<i>Let's get that aircra</i>ft <i>rolling.</i>

1250
01:28:37,845 --> 01:28:40,245
Not till I finish Knight.
Forget it. Let's go.

1251
01:29:09,177 --> 01:29:12,305
You'd better let me take over.
Your reflexes can't handle it.

1252
01:29:12,380 --> 01:29:16,146
<i>It's two out in the bottom</i>
<i>of the ninth, KITT.</i>
<i>I'll finish the game.</i>

1253
01:29:30,398 --> 01:29:33,526
[Engine Powering Down]

1254
01:30:01,095 --> 01:30:03,791
Run for the hangar.
We've gotta find another way out.

1255
01:30:03,865 --> 01:30:06,595
I'll get you a way out of here
that nothing can stop.

1256
01:30:07,902 --> 01:30:09,961
Tanya, come back here.

1257
01:30:11,239 --> 01:30:13,230
You lose, Michael.

1258
01:30:13,307 --> 01:30:15,172
No, Tanya. Don't!

1259
01:30:15,243 --> 01:30:16,335
The windows are...

1260
01:30:19,781 --> 01:30:21,874
<i>[Sirens Wailing]</i>

1261
01:30:30,625 --> 01:30:32,650
It's over, KITT.

1262
01:30:32,727 --> 01:30:34,718
It's all yours.

1263
01:30:35,863 --> 01:30:38,855
I'm getting you to a hospital
as soon as possible.

1264
01:30:50,778 --> 01:30:53,975
<i>[Maggie]</i>
<i>Michael, are you sure you're all right?</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

1265
01:30:54,048 --> 01:30:57,449
I'm a little stiff, a little sore,
but the doc says I'm mobile.

1266
01:30:58,486 --> 01:31:00,545
That's good.

1267
01:31:01,622 --> 01:31:04,523
I don't know
what I'm gonna do with Buddy
now that you're leaving.

1268
01:31:04,592 --> 01:31:06,719
Oh, I'd keep him.
He's a real good kid.

1269
01:31:06,794 --> 01:31:08,887
You know what I mean.

1270
01:31:09,997 --> 01:31:12,932
He needs a man.
I can see that now. L...

1271
01:31:14,402 --> 01:31:17,667
I guess I thought
I could just go on not caring.

1272
01:31:20,041 --> 01:31:21,975
And not looking.

1273
01:31:22,043 --> 01:31:23,977
Stupid, huh?

1274
01:31:24,045 --> 01:31:27,674
Here I had a prime candidate
right under my nose, and l...

1275
01:31:27,748 --> 01:31:29,739
I chased him away.

1276
01:31:29,817 --> 01:31:32,411
Ah, don't consider it
a permanent condition.

1277
01:31:33,488 --> 01:31:35,888
You mean that?

1278
01:31:35,957 --> 01:31:38,517
I mean, you might
come back and visit us sometime?

1279
01:31:39,660 --> 01:31:41,651
Tell Buddy it's a promise.

1280
01:31:44,165 --> 01:31:46,133
Oh.

1281
01:31:53,441 --> 01:31:57,309
You know, he, uh...
he was hoping you'd take him
for one last ride in your car.

1282
01:31:57,378 --> 01:32:01,542
<i>Yeah, well, that might be</i>
<i>one small problem.</i>

1283
01:32:01,616 --> 01:32:04,141
Only you could have
dented this car.

1284
01:32:04,218 --> 01:32:07,483
Hey. I'm sorry.
Nothing's perfect.

1285
01:32:07,555 --> 01:32:10,422
When do I get it back?
Who said anything
about getting it back?

1286
01:32:10,491 --> 01:32:13,619
Devon, it's my car.
I have the registration.

1287
01:32:13,694 --> 01:32:15,685
Don't remind me.

1288
01:32:15,763 --> 01:32:19,062
You know, I'd like to be
getting on with my work soon.

1289
01:32:24,906 --> 01:32:28,137
Very well.
Step aboard. We'll discuss it.

1290
01:32:35,983 --> 01:32:38,713
Now then, about my car.

1291
01:32:39,820 --> 01:32:44,314
Well, simply stated,
Wilton Knight was my friend
as well as my employer.

1292
01:32:44,392 --> 01:32:48,920
And my legacy is to see
that his final dream is faithfully pursued,
like it or not.

1293
01:32:48,996 --> 01:32:51,157
Your options are still open.

1294
01:32:51,232 --> 01:32:54,599
- You don't have to...
- Devon, the old man wanted me.

1295
01:32:54,669 --> 01:32:56,603
It was his dying request.

1296
01:32:56,671 --> 01:32:59,265
Yes, to rid the world
ofTanya and her friends.

1297
01:32:59,340 --> 01:33:02,104
But the rest of his dream
would bore you to tears.

1298
01:33:02,176 --> 01:33:05,839
<i>The majority of our activity here</i>
<i>involves legal research,</i>

1299
01:33:05,913 --> 01:33:09,371
class-action suits...
strictly bureaucratic stuff.

1300
01:33:09,450 --> 01:33:12,112
- What else?
- What else?

1301
01:33:12,186 --> 01:33:16,520
- Yeah, the part he wanted me for.
- Well, Mr. Knight also believed that
under certain circumstances,

1302
01:33:16,591 --> 01:33:19,617
direct action might be
the only feasible solution.

1303
01:33:19,694 --> 01:33:22,857
<i>That's what the Knight 2000</i>
<i>was designed for.</i>

1304
01:33:22,930 --> 01:33:27,890
The pilot program consists
of one man and one car.
Absurd really.

1305
01:33:27,969 --> 01:33:30,995
<i>I mean, who would want to</i>
<i>take on such a thing?</i>

1306
01:33:31,072 --> 01:33:34,064
I was supposed to be
that man, wasn't I?

1307
01:33:34,141 --> 01:33:36,905
Well, he seemed to feel that you were
singularly well-qualified...

1308
01:33:36,978 --> 01:33:39,139
<i>to</i> "<i>go it alone, '</i>'<i>as he put it.</i>

1309
01:33:39,213 --> 01:33:43,616
But who could expect it of you?
I mean, you barely came through
this misadventure with your life.

1310
01:33:43,684 --> 01:33:46,448
Not to mention the damage
to the Knight 2000.

1311
01:33:46,520 --> 01:33:52,117
I spent years of my life fighting
criminals of one type or another who always
had the upper hand, and now this.

1312
01:33:52,193 --> 01:33:55,822
<i>It's a loner's dream.</i>
<i>It's been handed to me</i>
<i>on a silver platter.</i>

1313
01:33:55,896 --> 01:33:59,229
The world's most fantastic car.

1314
01:33:59,300 --> 01:34:02,599
<i>All the money and all the resources</i>
<i>of the Knight Foundation.</i>

1315
01:34:03,938 --> 01:34:07,840
And most of all,
the best chance I'll ever get
to prove that one man...

1316
01:34:07,908 --> 01:34:09,899
really can make a difference.

1317
01:34:09,977 --> 01:34:13,674
I was afraid
that would be your attitude.

1318
01:34:14,715 --> 01:34:16,706
Well,

1319
01:34:18,219 --> 01:34:20,847
shall we drink to what may be
the start of, um...

1320
01:34:20,921 --> 01:34:22,855
Of what?

1321
01:34:22,923 --> 01:34:24,914
One man's dream.

1322
01:34:26,327 --> 01:34:28,420
And to our future.

1323
01:34:28,496 --> 01:34:31,863
No matter who it may
take us up against... or where.

1324
01:34:44,211 --> 01:34:47,703
<i>[Wilton]</i>
<i>One man</i> can <i>make a difference, Michael.</i>

1325
01:34:50,351 --> 01:34:55,015
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Michael Knight,</i>
<i>a lone crusader in a dangerous world,</i>

1326
01:34:55,089 --> 01:34:58,081
<i>the world of the Knight Rider.</i>

